The registrar has no jurisdiction to determine, on the passing of executor's accounts, any questions as to which assets are comprised in a particular estate: In the Will of Sarina (1925) 42 WN (NSW) 186. But the registrar otherwise has authority to allow executor's accounts (see SCR Pt 78 
r 94(3)
). There is therefore no necessity in the ordinary case to apply to the court for the passing of accounts, and the costs of any such application will be disallowed: Re Ewer (1903) 4 SR (NSW) 240; 20 WN (NSW) 254 ; followed In the Will of Walker (1915) 32 WN (NSW) 95.
